
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Phishing Awareness</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        .container {
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        p {
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .warning {
            color: #e74c3c;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .example-list {
            list-style: disc;
            padding-left: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .cta-button {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #e74c3c;
            color: #fff;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-weight: bold;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }
        .cta-button:hover {
            background-color: #c0392b;
        }
        @keyframes fadeIn {
            0% { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
            100% { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
        }
        .animated {
            opacity: 0;
            animation: fadeIn 1s ease forwards;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Phishing Awareness</h1>
        <p class="warning">Beware of Phishing Attacks!</p>
        <p>Phishing is a fraudulent attempt to obtain sensitive information by disguising as a trustworthy entity. Here's how you could have fallen into a trap:</p>
        <ol class="example-list">
            <li>You received an email or message that seemed urgent, asking for your login credentials.</li>
            <li>The sender's email address or URL looked slightly different from the legitimate source.</li>
            <li>The email contained suspicious links that redirected you to a fake website.</li>
            <li>You were promised rewards or threatened with consequences to manipulate your actions.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Remember to <span class="warning">never</span> share personal or sensitive information through unsolicited emails or messages. Always verify the source and be cautious of unexpected requests.</p>
        <a class="cta-button animated" href="#">Learn More</a>
    </div>
    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
            const ctaButton = document.querySelector('.cta-button');
            ctaButton.classList.add('animated');
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
